The field is composed of three elements.

15:45.400 --> 15:48.920
First, phi, which is scalar intelligibility or semantic bandwidth.

15:49.100 --> 15:49.320
Okay.

15:49.500 --> 15:52.000
Second, V, which is directed agency flow.

15:52.220 --> 15:54.960
And third, S, which represents entropy density.

15:55.240 --> 15:58.600
Entropy meaning chaos, disorder, and uncertainty.

15:58.600 --> 15:59.200
Yes.

15:59.860 --> 16:03.140
And the authors make a staggering, provocative claim here.

16:03.660 --> 16:05.240
They argue that trust is physical.

16:05.760 --> 16:10.900
Trust is mathematically defined as the controlled permeability of entropy between agents.

16:11.360 --> 16:14.820
In their equations, it's denoted by the Greek letter kappa.

16:15.020 --> 16:20.580
Permeability, meaning how much I allow my geometric boundaries to be open to your chaos and vice versa.

16:20.880 --> 16:23.240
Which leads to the paradox of precaution.

16:23.240 --> 16:30.440
The prevailing zeitgeist in AI safety today relies heavily on absolute control, containment, and surveillance.

16:30.760 --> 16:30.840
Right.

16:31.040 --> 16:32.420
The AI in a box theory.

