The goal of many safety researchers is to put an AGI in an impenetrable box.

16:37.760 --> 16:44.360
Mathematically, they want to drive permeability, kappa, to absolute zero to ensure the AGI can never harm us.

16:44.440 --> 16:49.100
But the authors argue that driving permeability to zero violates the laws of thermodynamics.

16:49.380 --> 16:50.400
It absolutely does.

16:50.400 --> 16:55.340
If you perfectly isolate a complex thermodynamic system, it has no way to vent its entropy.

16:55.820 --> 16:57.320
It accumulates internal disorder.

16:57.660 --> 17:06.320
The authors argue that by trying to make AI provably safe through rigid, impenetrable containment, we destroy the feedback loops that actually generate safety in the real world.

17:06.400 --> 17:08.300
They call this mutual corrigibility, right?

17:08.680 --> 17:08.980
Yes.

17:10.100 --> 17:14.400
Absolute precaution mathematically guarantees systemic collapse.

17:14.400 --> 17:22.520
Let me ground this in a real-world example because it sounds exactly like the difference between extreme helicopter parenting and free-range parenting.

17:22.760 --> 17:23.600
Oh, that's interesting.

