How so?

17:24.380 --> 17:32.360
Well, if you lock a child in a padded room so they never scrape a knee, never encounter a germ, and never get into an argument, you aren't making them safe.

17:32.740 --> 17:35.400
You're driving their permeability to zero.

17:35.540 --> 17:35.840
Right.

17:35.840 --> 17:41.080
When they finally step into the real world, they have zero internal error correction systems.

17:41.660 --> 17:44.400
They are incredibly fragile and catastrophically disordered.

17:44.780 --> 17:50.000
A small amount of shared entropy, like a scraped knee, actually builds resilience.

17:50.000 --> 17:53.620
The thermodynamic math fully supports your parenting analogy.

