But the final paper brings us crashing back down to Earth to a startling, grounding realization about how all of this computation actually works at the absolute lowest level.

24:32.900 --> 24:35.440
It strips away everything we think we know about logic.

24:35.600 --> 24:39.260
It does. It introduces the concept of the universal operator machine.

24:39.260 --> 24:44.500
The core thesis is a direct quote from the source. Composition is more fundamental than typing.

24:45.040 --> 24:46.840
Which ties right back to the hook we started with today.

24:47.180 --> 24:58.800
It does. We humans are deeply attached to our syntax. We love our types, our proofs, our programming languages, and we especially love the concept of Boolean logic, the absolute certainty of true and false.

24:59.720 --> 25:03.440
But the Flyxion papers argue that all of this is merely a human compression.

25:03.680 --> 25:04.220
A compression.

