Yes, it's a psychological illusion. It's a user interface skin designed to make the raw machinery of the universe legible to the human brain.

25:12.400 --> 25:15.440
From the perspective of the machine, true and false do not exist.

25:16.160 --> 25:23.360
The execution engine of SpherePop doesn't care about Boolean logic. It doesn't care about fuzzy logic or neural networks or symbolic AI.

25:23.360 --> 25:30.020
At its absolute core, a program is just a directed, acyclic graph. A DAG.

25:30.280 --> 25:35.380
A DAG is essentially a massive flowchart where data only moves in one direction, forward through the nodes.

25:35.480 --> 25:46.360
Exactly. A logic gate like an AND gate or an OR gate, which we treat as the fundamental building blocks of computing, is not some privileged, magical, metaphysical entity.

25:46.360 --> 25:53.660
It's just an ordinary modular lookup function attached to a node in the graph. It takes an input, checks a table, and spits out an output.

25:54.080 --> 26:02.920
What about control flow? When a programmer writes an if-then statement or a while loop, that feels like logic making a decision, like the computer is actually thinking.

26:02.920 --> 26:09.880
The paper demonstrates that control flow is an illusion. It is just the physical geometry of the DAG.

26:10.320 --> 26:18.620
A branch in your code isn't a cognitive decision. It is just a node labeled SELECT that physically routes data down one wire instead of another.

26:19.240 --> 26:26.500
A loop isn't a continuous thought. It is just feedback. A physical wire routing an output back to a previous input node.

26:26.500 --> 26:36.200
This is a massive paradigm shift. You're saying that syntax, programming languages like Python or C++A, and even the concept of true and false, are essentially just human illusions.

26:36.620 --> 26:40.380
They are just UI skins over a universal composition graph.

26:40.440 --> 26:42.980
Yes. A computer does not think in true or false.

26:43.400 --> 26:48.340
SpherePop proves that Boolean logic is just one tiny, interchangeable library of operators.

26:48.340 --> 26:59.420
You could take the exact same geometric DAG, rip out the Boolean logic library, and plug in a fuzzy logic library, where truth isn't a binary one or zero, but a gradient, like 0.734.

26:59.700 --> 27:01.440
And the execution engine wouldn't crash.

27:01.720 --> 27:08.340
